apertium-morph

This software is licensed both under the GNU GPL license and under the
Apache license, see COPYING for further information. 

This software is provided as is, WITHOUT any guarantee, in the hope
that it will be useful.

(c) 2008 Universitat d'Alacant / Universidad de Alicante

---------------------------------------------------------------------

This package provides a set of tools and Java classes that allow the
Lucene text search engine to use morphological information to index
and search. To that end, the linguistic resources developed for the
Apertium open-source machine translation platform
(http://www.apertium.org) are used to extract morphological
information while indexing.

Comments on this software are VERY welcome, do not hesitate to write
me for comments, feedback or just to tell me that you found this
software useful.

If you use this software for research, or for any other particular
purpose, I would be very grateful if you could cite the following
research paper describing this software:

* Felipe Sánchez-Martínez, Mikel L. Forcada, Rafael C. Carrasco.
  Searching for linguistic phenomena in literary digital libraries. In
  Workshop on Information Access to Cultural Heritage at ECDL 2008,
  September 18, 2008, Århus, Denmark.


